rComments: He is a good lecturer and the slides and textbook provided are helpful. However, the final exam is way too long and unreasonable. The class average is C+.

Prof. Taback is amazing. He is empathetic to his students' learning, kind and approachable. His teaching style is very clear and well-organized. He introduces relevant examples and makes it easy to digest hard material. His course helped me understand (and LOVE) statistics! If you have the opportunity to take his class, you will not regret it.
This is a required course for me and Nathan got it interesting, although sometimes he can be very quick and hard to follow.
Very monotone and slow speaker. Not amusing to listen to for 2 hours straight
Good at explaining concepts and seems to genuinely care about teaching and students' learning. The course wasn't too hard either (the average was a B).
He shows you how stats is used in real examples.  Really enjoyed the class.  I now plan to take more stats classes.  Grading on midterm was really fair, but the final exam is hard.
Great prof!  Highly recommend taking his class ...
He's a good professor, and he's really nice and approachable. His tests and exams are fair and he gives you more than enough things to help you prepare for them.
Dr. Taback is amazing!! Always there to go over concepts again after class, tests are fair and marking is not too picky

He  is the worst professor I ever encountered. The average in the midterm was below 60%  and he still made the final harder then the midterm. My grade dropped by 14% because  of  the final. He could of marked harder and make the final easier. Zhou Zhou is much fairer and easier than this guy.

His slides are extremely long, unclear and sometimes does not know what he's doing. Struggles to answer some student's questions and spends too much time trying to solve it. Weekly quizzes are not useful and final exam was extremely hard.
He teaches alright but gives hard tests and final making it impossible to do well
